DevOps Basics:
building simple CI/CD pipeline:


1. Clone a project from Github and make a Dockerfile of it: Follow TrainwithShubham video,
2. Create a EC2 instance and install Jenkins on it: follow install Jenkins,
3. configure jenkins user to nopassword inside pipeline:
# Allow members of group sudo to execute any command
%sudo   ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
ubuntu ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL
jenkins ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

4. Install git plugin on jenkins

5. Create a shellscript on jenkins:
cd /home/ubuntu/django-todo-cicd
# Build the Docker image
sudo docker build . -t todo-app
sudo docker run -p 8000:8000 -d todo-app
